The Anatomy of Harpo Marx

by Wayne KoestenbaumWayne Koestenbaum




 
 All Formats & Editions



See All Formats & Editions





The Anatomy of Harpo Marx is a luxuriant, detailed play-by-play account of Harpo Marx’s physical movements as captured on screen. Wayne Koestenbaum guides us through the thirteen Marx Brothers films, from The Cocoanuts in 1929 to Love Happy in 1950, to focus on Harpo’s chief and yet heretofore unexplored attributehis profound/i>/i>/i>

